snippet.textDisplay: The bread dough needs to be knead, then rested, then knead again and THEN rolled /shaped a bit and then be put in the baking form. It sounds time consuming  but its not really. Knead means massaging and rolling the dough repetedly. It helps activate the yeast even more and helps to bind the ingredients even better. Letting it rise for a few hours AFET putting into a baking form is essential. If not it might me very compact and doughy even after baking. It looked wonderful but i hope my tips help.
snippet.textOriginal: The bread dough needs to be knead, then rested, then knead again and THEN rolled /shaped a bit and then be put in the baking form. It sounds time consuming  but its not really. Knead means massaging and rolling the dough repetedly. It helps activate the yeast even more and helps to bind the ingredients even better. Letting it rise for a few hours AFET putting into a baking form is essential. If not it might me very compact and doughy even after baking. It looked wonderful but i hope my tips help.
